WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.403 --> 00:00:06.387
(<i> peaceful theme playing</i>)

2
00:00:45.546 --> 00:00:46.845
Take them down!

3
00:00:50.351 --> 00:00:51.528
(gasps)

4
00:00:51.552 --> 00:00:52.784
Hyah!

5
00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:55.087
MEN:
Hyah!

6
00:00:56.457 --> 00:00:57.734
Kahlan!

7
00:00:57.758 --> 00:00:59.124
(gasps)

8
00:01:04.532 --> 00:01:06.498
(<i> exciting theme playing</i>)

9
00:01:10.737 --> 00:01:13.004
FANE:
Shoot her!

10
00:01:20.814 --> 00:01:22.559
(gasps)

11
00:01:22.583 --> 00:01:25.584
(<i> slow theme playing</i>)

12
00:01:34.261 --> 00:01:37.407
Hold on. Dennee!
Stay with me!

13
00:01:37.431 --> 00:01:38.830
We're almost there!

14
00:01:42.403 --> 00:01:44.403
(<i> violin theme playing</i>)

15
00:01:48.142 --> 00:01:49.308
(groans)

16
00:01:53.114 --> 00:01:54.379
Hyah!

17
00:01:56.783 --> 00:01:58.584
KAHLAN:
Dennee!

18
00:02:01.455 --> 00:02:04.456
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

19
00:02:09.796 --> 00:02:11.774
(panting)

20
00:02:11.798 --> 00:02:13.332
Dennee.

21
00:02:14.235 --> 00:02:16.213
Dennee.

22
00:02:16.237 --> 00:02:18.281
(breathing heavily)

23
00:02:18.305 --> 00:02:19.549
Take it.

24
00:02:19.573 --> 00:02:21.784
Take the Book.

25
00:02:21.808 --> 00:02:24.421
This is more important than me.

26
00:02:24.445 --> 00:02:26.178
You know that.

27
00:02:28.749 --> 00:02:31.394
Please. Kahlan.

28
00:02:31.418 --> 00:02:32.817
(sniffs)

29
00:02:34.821 --> 00:02:39.603
May the Spirits protect you.
little sister.

30
00:02:39.627 --> 00:02:40.825
Kahlan.

31
00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:45.442
(horse whinnies)

32
00:02:45.466 --> 00:02:47.366
Go.

33
00:02:48.068 --> 00:02:49.834
Go.

34
00:02:51.205 --> 00:02:52.649
(sobs)

35
00:02:52.673 --> 00:02:53.838
(kiss)

36
00:02:54.841 --> 00:02:56.819
(sniffs)

37
00:02:56.843 --> 00:02:58.821
(gasps)

38
00:02:58.845 --> 00:03:02.325
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

39
00:03:02.349 --> 00:03:03.782
MEN:
Hyah!

40
00:03:09.723 --> 00:03:11.623
MEN:
Hyah!

41
00:03:16.063 --> 00:03:18.029
(panting)

42
00:03:24.638 --> 00:03:26.783
(horses whinny)

43
00:03:26.807 --> 00:03:31.020
FANE:
You've reached
the Boundary. Confessor.

44
00:03:31.044 --> 00:03:33.056
There is nowhere left to run.

45
00:03:33.080 --> 00:03:34.357
(horses whinny)

46
00:03:34.381 --> 00:03:35.814
Steady.

47
00:03:42.723 --> 00:03:44.356
MAN:
Steady. boy.

48
00:03:48.395 --> 00:03:50.562
(whinnies)
She's got magic!

49
00:04:00.841 --> 00:04:02.752
Ride to the garrison
at Kaldrith.

50
00:04:02.776 --> 00:04:05.222
Send word to Lord Rahl:

51
00:04:05.246 --> 00:04:09.025
The Confessor has broken
through the Boundary.

52
00:04:09.049 --> 00:04:10.293
Yes. sir.

53
00:04:10.317 --> 00:04:12.362
You three are coming with me.

54
00:04:12.386 --> 00:04:14.353
MAN:
But sir...

55
00:04:19.426 --> 00:04:22.594
(<i> suspenseful theme playing</i>)

56
00:04:29.035 --> 00:04:31.035
(<i> drum theme playing</i>)

57
00:04:33.073 --> 00:04:36.074
(<i> drum theme playing</i>)

58
00:05:06.307 --> 00:05:08.774
(hammer thumping)

59
00:05:12.245 --> 00:05:14.491
BOY:
Hi. Richard.

60
00:05:14.515 --> 00:05:16.293
Jared.
You're just in time.

61
00:05:16.317 --> 00:05:17.560
For what?

62
00:05:17.584 --> 00:05:19.551
You can be the first to cross.

63
00:05:22.656 --> 00:05:24.167
Don't worry. It's safe.

64
00:05:24.191 --> 00:05:26.770
(moos)
Oh. it's not me that's scared.

65
00:05:26.794 --> 00:05:28.427
It's... It's Lanie.

66
00:05:30.664 --> 00:05:32.074
Of course.

67
00:05:32.098 --> 00:05:34.577
(moos)
Smart cow.

68
00:05:34.601 --> 00:05:36.780
Never cross a bridge
that hasn't been tested.

69
00:05:36.804 --> 00:05:38.603
Come on. boy.

70
00:05:48.148 --> 00:05:50.660
I don't think Lanie
has anything to worry about.

71
00:05:50.684 --> 00:05:52.796
Thanks. Richard.

72
00:05:52.820 --> 00:05:54.197
Flynn. come.
(dog barks)

73
00:05:54.221 --> 00:05:55.432
Hungry. boy?

74
00:05:55.456 --> 00:05:57.166
Yeah. me too.

75
00:05:57.190 --> 00:05:59.023
Come on.

76
00:06:02.229 --> 00:06:04.229
(dog barks)

77
00:06:21.081 --> 00:06:24.483
(<i> vocal theme playing</i>)

78
00:06:35.796 --> 00:06:38.029
(grunts)

79
00:06:53.614 --> 00:06:55.614
(panting)

80
00:06:59.352 --> 00:07:01.753
Oh!

81
00:07:03.590 --> 00:07:06.035
(panting)

82
00:07:06.059 --> 00:07:07.759
(gasps)

83
00:07:17.971 --> 00:07:19.248
Stay back.

84
00:07:19.272 --> 00:07:20.439
Shoot her.

85
00:07:22.543 --> 00:07:24.186
(grunts)

86
00:07:24.210 --> 00:07:27.023
Leave her alone.

87
00:07:27.047 --> 00:07:28.758
You're making a mistake. boy.

88
00:07:28.782 --> 00:07:32.216
This girl is dangerous.

89
00:07:33.420 --> 00:07:35.598
Four men against one woman?

90
00:07:35.622 --> 00:07:37.767
I think she's the one in danger.

91
00:07:37.791 --> 00:07:41.103
You don't understand
what you're talking about.

92
00:07:41.127 --> 00:07:43.773
And this is not your fight.

93
00:07:43.797 --> 00:07:45.642
So be smart

94
00:07:45.666 --> 00:07:47.644
and go home.

95
00:07:47.668 --> 00:07:49.446
I'm not going anywhere.

96
00:07:49.470 --> 00:07:50.735
(grunts)

97
00:07:53.574 --> 00:07:55.284
FANE:
Easy.

98
00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:56.786
Do not let her grasp you.

99
00:07:56.810 --> 00:07:58.610
(grunting)

100
00:07:59.613 --> 00:08:01.813
(<i> vocal theme playing</i>)

101
00:08:12.425 --> 00:08:14.403
(grunting)

102
00:08:14.427 --> 00:08:16.461
(men grunting. swords clanging)

103
00:08:26.106 --> 00:08:27.572
Ah!

104
00:08:35.281 --> 00:08:39.417
It's over for you. Confessor.

105
00:08:42.789 --> 00:08:45.023
(both grunting)

106
00:08:52.799 --> 00:08:55.678
(screaming)

107
00:08:55.702 --> 00:08:57.480
(grunting)

108
00:08:57.504 --> 00:08:59.782
(fane yells)

109
00:08:59.806 --> 00:09:01.784
(panting)

110
00:09:01.808 --> 00:09:04.475
(gasps)

111
00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:11.315
(grunts)

112
00:09:12.352 --> 00:09:13.952
(<i> bell theme playing</i>)

113
00:09:18.592 --> 00:09:20.058
Your hand is bleeding.

114
00:09:27.534 --> 00:09:29.445
Let me take you to my father's.

115
00:09:29.469 --> 00:09:31.069
We can dress the wound.

116
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.477
Did I do something wrong?

117
00:09:41.048 --> 00:09:43.325
No.

118
00:09:43.349 --> 00:09:45.762
I'm just...

119
00:09:45.786 --> 00:09:47.597
not used to people touching me.

120
00:09:47.621 --> 00:09:50.354
I'm sorry.

121
00:09:51.658 --> 00:09:53.291
It's all right.

122
00:10:05.105 --> 00:10:07.005
I have to go.

123
00:10:09.209 --> 00:10:10.453
Where?

124
00:10:10.477 --> 00:10:12.789
There's someone I need to find.

125
00:10:12.813 --> 00:10:14.457
Who? Maybe I
can help you.

126
00:10:14.481 --> 00:10:15.625
Don't worry about me.

127
00:10:15.649 --> 00:10:17.082
I can take care of myself.

128
00:10:20.053 --> 00:10:22.348
Why were these men chasing you?

129
00:10:22.372 --> 00:10:24.067
You always ask
this many questions?

130
00:10:24.091 --> 00:10:25.501
I just saved your life.

131
00:10:25.525 --> 00:10:27.603
The least you could do
is tell me what happened.

132
00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:30.628
Actually. I saved yours.

133
00:10:32.482 --> 00:10:36.161
When you touched that man.

134
00:10:36.185 --> 00:10:37.685
what did you do to him?

135
00:10:39.822 --> 00:10:41.689
Hey.

136
00:10:43.260 --> 00:10:45.226
You want to know
what I did to that man?

137
00:10:47.664 --> 00:10:49.597
Try and follow me
and you'll find out.

138
00:11:00.277 --> 00:11:02.644
(panting)

139
00:11:04.247 --> 00:11:07.598
(<i> suspenseful theme playing</i>)

140
00:11:19.813 --> 00:11:21.312
Ah!

141
00:11:24.818 --> 00:11:28.186
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

142
00:11:30.674 --> 00:11:33.808
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

143
00:11:35.411 --> 00:11:37.411
(footsteps approaching)

144
00:11:42.218 --> 00:11:44.597
Drop the weapons.

145
00:11:44.621 --> 00:11:47.767
I said drop them.

146
00:11:47.791 --> 00:11:49.234
On whose authority?

147
00:11:49.258 --> 00:11:50.670
The Councilor's Guards.

148
00:11:50.694 --> 00:11:52.627
which would be me.

149
00:11:55.365 --> 00:11:56.631
and them.

150
00:12:02.038 --> 00:12:03.571
(weapons thud)

151
00:12:05.675 --> 00:12:08.187
Now. tell me what happened here.

152
00:12:08.211 --> 00:12:10.389
This Councilor you guard.

153
00:12:10.413 --> 00:12:12.692
is he the ruler
of this province?

154
00:12:12.716 --> 00:12:14.059
He is.

155
00:12:14.083 --> 00:12:17.652
Then I will tell
my story to him.

156
00:12:18.688 --> 00:12:21.667
<i>My name is Ranssyn Fane.</i>

157
00:12:21.691 --> 00:12:24.670
a commander
of the D'Haran Forces.

158
00:12:24.694 --> 00:12:26.438
D'Hara?

159
00:12:26.462 --> 00:12:28.073
But that's...

160
00:12:28.097 --> 00:12:31.644
I have come from the Midlands.

161
00:12:31.668 --> 00:12:34.148
What other fairy-tales
do you have to tell us?

162
00:12:35.705 --> 00:12:37.216
Forgive our skepticism.

163
00:12:37.240 --> 00:12:38.684
but no one's
crossed the Boundary

164
00:12:38.708 --> 00:12:40.141
in hundreds of years.

165
00:12:42.178 --> 00:12:45.090
The woman I'm
pursuing found a way.

166
00:12:45.114 --> 00:12:47.693
How?

167
00:12:47.717 --> 00:12:49.328
She is a witch.

168
00:12:49.352 --> 00:12:50.730
(<i> suspenseful theme playing</i>)

169
00:12:50.754 --> 00:12:52.565
Come on. Shar.

170
00:12:52.589 --> 00:12:53.766
Come on.

171
00:12:53.790 --> 00:12:56.068
Okay.

172
00:12:56.092 --> 00:12:57.291
There we go.

173
00:13:01.965 --> 00:13:03.230
There.

174
00:13:09.405 --> 00:13:11.050
(groans)

175
00:13:11.074 --> 00:13:12.506
(<i> suspenseful theme playing</i>)

176
00:13:17.213 --> 00:13:19.659
(<i> flute theme playing</i>)

177
00:13:19.683 --> 00:13:21.661
GEORGE:
<i>You're finished. Richard.</i>

178
00:13:21.685 --> 00:13:23.763
I've got you beat in two moves.

179
00:13:23.787 --> 00:13:25.397
RICHARD: Dad...
Come on.

180
00:13:25.421 --> 00:13:28.333
let's get the bloodbath
over with. so we can eat.

181
00:13:28.357 --> 00:13:29.501
Dad.

182
00:13:29.525 --> 00:13:32.304
Son.

183
00:13:32.328 --> 00:13:33.573
What is it?

184
00:13:33.597 --> 00:13:35.207
What's happened?

185
00:13:35.231 --> 00:13:37.142
FANE:
<i>Her magic is more powerful</i>

186
00:13:37.166 --> 00:13:38.678
than you could possibly imagine.

187
00:13:38.702 --> 00:13:41.413
She used it to cross
into your territory.

188
00:13:41.437 --> 00:13:43.248
And she had help.

189
00:13:43.272 --> 00:13:46.686
From someone on this side
of the Boundary.

190
00:13:46.710 --> 00:13:49.711
He was wearing this.

191
00:13:56.586 --> 00:13:58.698
You recognize it.

192
00:13:58.722 --> 00:14:00.421
It belongs to my brother.

193
00:14:03.392 --> 00:14:06.105
RICHARD:
A poison vine
I've never seen before.

194
00:14:06.129 --> 00:14:08.574
that glowing thing in her hand.

195
00:14:08.598 --> 00:14:12.444
what she did to that
man who attacked her.

196
00:14:12.468 --> 00:14:14.680
it was magic. wasn't it?

197
00:14:14.704 --> 00:14:16.949
Hm.

198
00:14:16.973 --> 00:14:19.118
There's no magic
this side of the Boundary.

199
00:14:19.142 --> 00:14:20.452
She and these men.

200
00:14:20.476 --> 00:14:23.022
they're from the Midlands.

201
00:14:23.046 --> 00:14:24.389
That can't be right.

202
00:14:24.413 --> 00:14:26.458
I was a fool to think
this day would never come.

203
00:14:26.482 --> 00:14:27.627
What day?

204
00:14:27.651 --> 00:14:29.662
Richard.
you know that I love you.

205
00:14:29.686 --> 00:14:31.664
Dad. of course.

206
00:14:31.688 --> 00:14:33.633
(horse whinnies outside)

207
00:14:33.657 --> 00:14:35.690
(men shouting outside)

208
00:14:37.326 --> 00:14:39.238
(horses galloping)

209
00:14:39.262 --> 00:14:41.796
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

210
00:14:45.568 --> 00:14:48.147
Dad. that's him. That's the guy
who fell off the cliff.

211
00:14:48.171 --> 00:14:49.682
You have to leave. Now.

212
00:14:49.706 --> 00:14:51.216
Out the back
before they get here.

213
00:14:51.240 --> 00:14:52.518
Michael and Chase are with him.

214
00:14:52.542 --> 00:14:53.686
They can help.
Go.

215
00:14:53.710 --> 00:14:55.988
Where?
Blackthorn Hill. Find Zedd.

216
00:14:56.012 --> 00:14:57.289
That crazy old man?

217
00:14:57.313 --> 00:14:58.691
Zedd will explain everything.

218
00:14:58.715 --> 00:15:00.726
He talks to his chickens. Why?
Tell him I sent you.

219
00:15:00.750 --> 00:15:02.194
He'll know why. Just go.

220
00:15:02.218 --> 00:15:03.696
I'll meet you there
as soon as I can.

221
00:15:03.720 --> 00:15:05.286
Dad...

222
00:15:06.389 --> 00:15:09.657
Richard. you have to go.

223
00:15:11.527 --> 00:15:13.372
Now.

224
00:15:13.396 --> 00:15:15.196
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

225
00:15:22.672 --> 00:15:25.151
(pounding on door)

226
00:15:25.175 --> 00:15:28.042
I haven't seen him
since breakfast time.

227
00:15:30.146 --> 00:15:34.193
He said he was gonna
work on the new bridge.

228
00:15:34.217 --> 00:15:36.495
Are you sure he didn't
come home during the day.

229
00:15:36.519 --> 00:15:40.700
uh. maybe while you were
out gathering firewood?

230
00:15:40.724 --> 00:15:42.690
I haven't left the house.

231
00:15:44.660 --> 00:15:48.674
MICHAEL:
Take Commander Fane
and find him.

232
00:15:48.698 --> 00:15:50.676
If Richard's in
trouble. I want to help.

233
00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:52.678
If we all follow
a different trail...

234
00:15:52.702 --> 00:15:54.680
Better if you stay here.

235
00:15:54.704 --> 00:15:57.683
He could still come back.

236
00:15:57.707 --> 00:15:59.118
and he may be frightened.

237
00:15:59.142 --> 00:16:00.319
Or worse.

238
00:16:00.343 --> 00:16:01.787
What do you mean?

239
00:16:01.811 --> 00:16:04.724
The witch has the power
to put him under her control.

240
00:16:04.748 --> 00:16:06.658
and if she does.

241
00:16:06.682 --> 00:16:08.493
he's gonna need his father here

242
00:16:08.517 --> 00:16:10.684
to try and talk
some sense to him.

243
00:16:12.388 --> 00:16:16.657
You should leave some of your
men. in case it goes badly.

244
00:16:19.362 --> 00:16:21.006
MICHAEL:
Chase. post two men outside.

245
00:16:21.030 --> 00:16:23.642
Take the rest down
to the South Bridge.

246
00:16:23.666 --> 00:16:25.666
(door opens)

247
00:16:29.005 --> 00:16:30.449
What is it?

248
00:16:30.473 --> 00:16:32.351
Michael. why are you
so quick to believe

249
00:16:32.375 --> 00:16:33.685
a stranger from the Midlands?

250
00:16:33.709 --> 00:16:38.157
Because Richard does
things without thinking.

251
00:16:38.181 --> 00:16:39.358
He always has.

252
00:16:39.382 --> 00:16:40.760
since he was a little boy.

253
00:16:40.784 --> 00:16:42.327
And you've always protected him.

254
00:16:42.351 --> 00:16:43.528
He's my son.

255
00:16:43.552 --> 00:16:45.519
He's your brother.

256
00:16:46.489 --> 00:16:47.767
Please. Michael.

257
00:16:47.791 --> 00:16:49.690
make sure he doesn't get hurt.

258
00:16:51.694 --> 00:16:55.107
Stay here. If he comes
back. bring him to me.

259
00:16:55.131 --> 00:16:57.977
We'll find out
what really happened.

260
00:16:58.001 --> 00:17:01.046
(footsteps receding)

261
00:17:01.070 --> 00:17:03.715
ZEDD:
<i>It's a bad omen. Clara.</i>

262
00:17:03.739 --> 00:17:06.218
(coos)

263
00:17:06.242 --> 00:17:10.389
A could in the shape of
a horn from the far east.

264
00:17:10.413 --> 00:17:12.925
I'm betting a month of
suppers it'll bring no good

265
00:17:12.949 --> 00:17:14.326
before the sun comes up.

266
00:17:14.350 --> 00:17:15.627
(Clara clucks)

267
00:17:15.651 --> 00:17:17.263
Oh. no. no. no.

268
00:17:17.287 --> 00:17:20.632
Don't worry. Clara.
Supper will never be you.

269
00:17:20.656 --> 00:17:22.323
KAHLAN:
I need your help. Wizard.

270
00:17:25.661 --> 00:17:29.108
Sorry. uh.
I'm as deaf as a peach

271
00:17:29.132 --> 00:17:31.498
and as naked as a baby bird.

272
00:17:34.103 --> 00:17:36.648
What did you say?

273
00:17:36.672 --> 00:17:40.652
I asked the Great Wizard
Zeddicus Zu'l Zorander

274
00:17:40.676 --> 00:17:42.188
for his assistance.

275
00:17:42.212 --> 00:17:43.677
No.

276
00:17:45.248 --> 00:17:47.648
I think you have me confused
with somebody else.

277
00:17:49.118 --> 00:17:51.463
There's no confusion.

278
00:17:51.487 --> 00:17:53.687
I had help finding you.

279
00:18:05.634 --> 00:18:08.447
Well. it was good
while it lasted.

280
00:18:08.471 --> 00:18:12.218
Nice quiet couple of decades.

281
00:18:12.242 --> 00:18:15.020
And now time is up.

282
00:18:15.044 --> 00:18:16.324
Bring me to the Seeker.

283
00:18:21.484 --> 00:18:24.230
(horse approaching)

284
00:18:24.254 --> 00:18:26.254
(<i> exciting theme playing</i>)

285
00:18:27.656 --> 00:18:29.957
(breathing heavily)

286
00:18:35.564 --> 00:18:37.243
RICHARD:
You.

287
00:18:37.267 --> 00:18:40.334
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

288
00:18:43.740 --> 00:18:45.740
(chanting in ancient tongue)

289
00:18:49.044 --> 00:18:50.978
(Richard breathing heavily)

290
00:18:52.415 --> 00:18:54.415
(panting)

291
00:18:58.053 --> 00:19:01.166
(grunts)
(Zedd yells)

292
00:19:01.190 --> 00:19:02.990
(gasping)

293
00:19:07.162 --> 00:19:09.162
(panting)

294
00:19:10.733 --> 00:19:12.077
(Richard groans)

295
00:19:12.101 --> 00:19:13.467
His fever's broken.

296
00:19:14.570 --> 00:19:16.404
Now take me to the Seeker.

297
00:19:17.473 --> 00:19:18.939
He's here.

298
00:19:21.511 --> 00:19:22.743
Him?

299
00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:26.157
But... But he's... What?

300
00:19:26.181 --> 00:19:27.559
Not good enough?

301
00:19:27.583 --> 00:19:29.327
You wanted a
Seeker. there he is.

302
00:19:29.351 --> 00:19:32.464
If he's not up to your standard.
well. that's fine by me.

303
00:19:32.488 --> 00:19:33.932
Find yourself another.

304
00:19:33.956 --> 00:19:35.534
RICHARD:
Seeker?

305
00:19:35.558 --> 00:19:37.358
What are you talking about?

306
00:19:42.131 --> 00:19:43.531
You never told him?

307
00:19:45.601 --> 00:19:47.713
You were supposed to train him.

308
00:19:47.737 --> 00:19:49.581
Prepare him.

309
00:19:49.605 --> 00:19:52.350
What have you been doing
for the last 20 years?

310
00:19:52.374 --> 00:19:55.454
Letting him catch worms.

311
00:19:55.478 --> 00:19:57.989
Steal apples.
Skin his knees.

312
00:19:58.013 --> 00:20:00.592
Find out what makes
his heart beat faster.

313
00:20:00.616 --> 00:20:04.095
My sister gave her life
to make sure that I got here.

314
00:20:04.119 --> 00:20:06.598
to make sure that I put
the Book in the Seeker's hands.

315
00:20:06.622 --> 00:20:09.067
and he's catching worms?
Never knew a great man

316
00:20:09.091 --> 00:20:10.602
who didn't have
dirt under his nails.

317
00:20:10.626 --> 00:20:12.704
And while he's getting
his nails dirty.

318
00:20:12.728 --> 00:20:15.607
did it ever occur to you to
give him the slightest inkling

319
00:20:15.631 --> 00:20:19.377
that he is the first true Seeker
in the last thousand years?

320
00:20:19.401 --> 00:20:21.279
He has a destiny.

321
00:20:21.303 --> 00:20:24.249
Who are you to
decide a man's destiny?

322
00:20:24.273 --> 00:20:26.351
It's not me.
It's the Prophecy.

323
00:20:26.375 --> 00:20:28.353
Prophecy be damned!

324
00:20:28.377 --> 00:20:30.422
I averted the Prophecy
when I brought him here.

325
00:20:30.446 --> 00:20:33.191
Until you opened up a nice
little door in the Boundary

326
00:20:33.215 --> 00:20:34.726
and said. "Right
this way to the Seeker.

327
00:20:34.750 --> 00:20:36.194
ladies and gentlemen."

328
00:20:36.218 --> 00:20:37.384
RICHARD:
Stop.

329
00:20:38.688 --> 00:20:40.532
What are you talking about?

330
00:20:40.556 --> 00:20:42.389
And what's a Seeker?

331
00:20:45.194 --> 00:20:48.139
If you were so sure
you averted the Prophecy.

332
00:20:48.163 --> 00:20:51.443
that he was gonna live
a nice. peaceful life.

333
00:20:51.467 --> 00:20:54.034
why did you stay near
him all these years?

334
00:20:55.404 --> 00:20:57.415
Tell him the truth.

335
00:20:57.439 --> 00:20:59.540
Tell him who he is.

336
00:21:03.613 --> 00:21:05.278
(sighs)

337
00:21:10.052 --> 00:21:15.601
First you need to know
about a man named Darken Rahl.

338
00:21:15.625 --> 00:21:18.436
<i>if he is a man. and not
some twisted wraith of evil</i>

339
00:21:18.460 --> 00:21:20.205
<i>brought forth
from the underworld</i>

340
00:21:20.229 --> 00:21:25.443
<i>to shatter the
dreams of humankind.</i>

341
00:21:25.467 --> 00:21:29.314
<i>Twenty-three years ago. a great
prophet spoke on his deathbed</i>

342
00:21:29.338 --> 00:21:31.717
<i>of the birth of a true Seeker.</i>

343
00:21:31.741 --> 00:21:34.987
<i>A child whose destiny would
be to seek out and kill</i>

344
00:21:35.011 --> 00:21:36.655
<i>the greatest evil of all:</i>

345
00:21:36.679 --> 00:21:38.390
<i>Darken Rahl.</i>

346
00:21:38.414 --> 00:21:41.326
(woman yelling)

347
00:21:41.350 --> 00:21:44.329
<i>And with his last breath.
the prophet named the town</i>

348
00:21:44.353 --> 00:21:47.132
<i>in which the child
had been born.</i>

349
00:21:47.156 --> 00:21:48.400
(men yelling)

350
00:21:48.424 --> 00:21:50.569
<i>Rahl sent his assassins.</i>

351
00:21:50.593 --> 00:21:52.504
(woman screaming)

352
00:21:52.528 --> 00:21:55.607
(men grunting)

353
00:21:55.631 --> 00:21:58.677
(woman screams)

354
00:21:58.701 --> 00:22:00.378
ZEDD:
<i>And in one night.</i>

355
00:22:00.402 --> 00:22:04.049
<i>they murdered every first-born
son in Brennidon...</i>

356
00:22:04.073 --> 00:22:06.339
(screaming)

357
00:22:07.342 --> 00:22:09.342
save one.

358
00:22:10.980 --> 00:22:12.512
(horse whinnying)

359
00:22:15.017 --> 00:22:19.330
<i>Your mother gave birth
in the madness of the massacre.</i>

360
00:22:19.354 --> 00:22:23.557
<i>She was young.
She was weak.</i>

361
00:22:25.194 --> 00:22:28.073
She was still alive
when I took you

362
00:22:28.097 --> 00:22:30.097
from her arms.

363
00:22:31.133 --> 00:22:33.211
(crying)

364
00:22:33.235 --> 00:22:36.369
She kissed you. blessed you.

365
00:22:37.506 --> 00:22:40.586
My mother died when I was 10.

366
00:22:40.610 --> 00:22:44.790
Here. In Hartland.

367
00:22:44.814 --> 00:22:46.792
The woman you
knew as your mother

368
00:22:46.816 --> 00:22:50.062
raised you and loved you
as if you were her own.

369
00:22:50.086 --> 00:22:52.406
but she did not
give birth to you.

370
00:22:54.824 --> 00:22:56.735
I crossed the Boundary

371
00:22:56.759 --> 00:22:59.370
<i>at night. unseen.</i>

372
00:22:59.394 --> 00:23:02.674
<i>with you in my arms.</i>

373
00:23:02.698 --> 00:23:05.143
(thunder rumbling)

374
00:23:05.167 --> 00:23:08.313
<i>For weeks I watched. listened.</i>

375
00:23:08.337 --> 00:23:10.115
<i>read the clouds.</i>

376
00:23:10.139 --> 00:23:12.084
<i>and came to know
that in all the world</i>

377
00:23:12.108 --> 00:23:15.253
<i>there was no one kinder
than George and Mary Cypher.</i>

378
00:23:15.277 --> 00:23:17.990
<i>I told them your story.
and they took you</i>

379
00:23:18.014 --> 00:23:20.458
<i>into their home.
and into their hearts.</i>

380
00:23:20.482 --> 00:23:22.293
<i>And if I live to be
a thousand years old.</i>

381
00:23:22.317 --> 00:23:24.062
<i>I'll never make a wiser choice</i>

382
00:23:24.086 --> 00:23:26.353
<i>than picking them for the job.</i>

383
00:23:30.459 --> 00:23:32.337
RICHARD:
So...

384
00:23:32.361 --> 00:23:36.174
according to this fantasy.

385
00:23:36.198 --> 00:23:37.743
who's my real father?

386
00:23:37.767 --> 00:23:39.733
I don't know.

387
00:23:42.271 --> 00:23:44.482
And if you knew
my parents so well.

388
00:23:44.506 --> 00:23:46.284
why didn't I ever
see you with them?

389
00:23:46.308 --> 00:23:47.519
Why haven't you talked to me?

390
00:23:47.543 --> 00:23:49.254
I kept myself apart.

391
00:23:49.278 --> 00:23:52.257
close enough to keep watch
over you. but far enough away

392
00:23:52.281 --> 00:23:55.193
so that if Darken Rahl
ever found his way to me.

393
00:23:55.217 --> 00:23:58.997
I wouldn't be a blazing arrow
pointing the way to you.

394
00:23:59.021 --> 00:24:02.656
Apparently. that's
what Confessors are for.

395
00:24:04.660 --> 00:24:05.993
Confessors?

396
00:24:09.364 --> 00:24:13.311
An ancient order of women
sworn to find the truth.

397
00:24:13.335 --> 00:24:16.982
no matter how hard
people may try to hide it.

398
00:24:17.006 --> 00:24:20.686
And if a Seeker should arise.

399
00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:23.143
to protect him with her life.

400
00:24:26.082 --> 00:24:27.347
My name is Kahlan.

401
00:24:29.618 --> 00:24:33.264
I'm sorry for
threatening you today.

402
00:24:33.288 --> 00:24:35.655
You did save my life.

403
00:24:39.128 --> 00:24:41.195
I came here to bring you this.

404
00:24:44.767 --> 00:24:46.178
RICHARD:
A book?

405
00:24:46.202 --> 00:24:48.613
Not just any book.

406
00:24:48.637 --> 00:24:52.117
It's<i> The Book</i>
<i>of Counted Shadows.</i>

407
00:24:52.141 --> 00:24:55.253
It was written in a time
before remembering.

408
00:24:55.277 --> 00:24:57.689
For a thousand years.
it's been kept safe

409
00:24:57.713 --> 00:25:00.358
in the Wizard's Keep.
in Aydindril.

410
00:25:00.382 --> 00:25:02.293
But a month ago
the armies of Darken Rahl

411
00:25:02.317 --> 00:25:06.297
broke through our last defenses
in an attempt to steal it.

412
00:25:06.321 --> 00:25:07.933
Why?

413
00:25:07.957 --> 00:25:09.300
Because the Book contains

414
00:25:09.324 --> 00:25:11.603
the secrets of power.

415
00:25:11.627 --> 00:25:14.106
KAHLAN:
And if Darken Rahl gets it.

416
00:25:14.130 --> 00:25:17.743
he will use it to control
every corner of the world.

417
00:25:17.767 --> 00:25:20.127
and we would all
become his slaves.

418
00:25:25.707 --> 00:25:27.485
The Prophecy
says that the Seeker

419
00:25:27.509 --> 00:25:30.644
will use the Book
in his quest to defeat Rahl.

420
00:25:34.049 --> 00:25:35.382
Read it.

421
00:25:45.627 --> 00:25:49.540
Um. maybe this Seeker you're
looking for knows this language.

422
00:25:49.564 --> 00:25:53.344
but I don't.

423
00:25:53.368 --> 00:25:55.713
Try.

424
00:25:55.737 --> 00:25:57.104
(scoffs)

425
00:26:02.978 --> 00:26:05.679
(<i> suspenseful theme playing</i>)

426
00:26:08.083 --> 00:26:10.295
"The truth

427
00:26:10.319 --> 00:26:12.230
"of the words

428
00:26:12.254 --> 00:26:14.232
"of<i> The Book of Counted Shadows</i>

429
00:26:14.256 --> 00:26:17.424
can only be ensured
by a Confessor."

430
00:26:22.364 --> 00:26:23.741
How...?

431
00:26:23.765 --> 00:26:28.146
Because you are the true Seeker.

432
00:26:28.170 --> 00:26:30.337
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

433
00:26:32.641 --> 00:26:34.641
FANE:
That's a good blade
you've got there.

434
00:26:37.513 --> 00:26:38.657
I could use a tool like that.

435
00:26:38.681 --> 00:26:40.258
Where did you get it?

436
00:26:40.282 --> 00:26:41.981
Trader from down south.

437
00:26:44.052 --> 00:26:45.697
(chuckles)

438
00:26:45.721 --> 00:26:47.065
FANE:
What is it?

439
00:26:47.089 --> 00:26:48.655
Richard's trail ends here.

440
00:26:50.759 --> 00:26:52.671
We'll split up.

441
00:26:52.695 --> 00:26:54.695
Cover more ground.
Hyah!

442
00:26:56.332 --> 00:26:58.343
KAHLAN:
<i>Give him the Sword.</i>

443
00:26:58.367 --> 00:27:00.545
Name him.

444
00:27:00.569 --> 00:27:02.936
What sword?

445
00:27:04.506 --> 00:27:05.706
(gasps)

446
00:27:06.775 --> 00:27:08.709
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

447
00:27:10.279 --> 00:27:13.191
This is the Sword of Truth.

448
00:27:13.215 --> 00:27:17.229
ZEDD:
In anyone else's hands.
this is just a piece of steel.

449
00:27:17.253 --> 00:27:19.598
But in the Seeker's hands.

450
00:27:19.622 --> 00:27:22.467
bestows the power to fight evil.

451
00:27:22.491 --> 00:27:26.393
And with it
you will kill Darken Rahl.

452
00:27:28.664 --> 00:27:30.642
I'm not killing anybody.

453
00:27:30.666 --> 00:27:32.210
I don't even know either of you.

454
00:27:32.234 --> 00:27:33.978
For all I know.
this is some kind of trick.

455
00:27:34.002 --> 00:27:35.614
I'm not a Seeker.

456
00:27:35.638 --> 00:27:38.116
I don't want any book.
or any sword.

457
00:27:38.140 --> 00:27:39.317
Calm down. my boy.

458
00:27:39.341 --> 00:27:41.253
I'm not your boy.

459
00:27:41.277 --> 00:27:43.255
My father is George Cypher.

460
00:27:43.279 --> 00:27:44.456
and if any of this were true.

461
00:27:44.480 --> 00:27:45.657
he'd have told me.

462
00:27:45.681 --> 00:27:47.559
Now. get out of my way.
Richard. wait.

463
00:27:47.583 --> 00:27:50.762
ZEDD: Let him go.
What?

464
00:27:50.786 --> 00:27:53.365
He needs to find
the truth for himself.

465
00:27:53.389 --> 00:27:56.156
Until then. he cannot be named.

466
00:27:58.260 --> 00:27:59.526
FANE:
<i>Hyah!</i>

467
00:28:03.999 --> 00:28:05.732
(horse approaching)

468
00:28:15.611 --> 00:28:17.722
Your First Councilor needs
more men on the North Hill.

469
00:28:17.746 --> 00:28:19.658
He said I was to tell you

470
00:28:19.682 --> 00:28:22.316
to join him there.

471
00:28:24.653 --> 00:28:26.620
(horses galloping)

472
00:28:34.330 --> 00:28:36.330
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

473
00:28:39.134 --> 00:28:41.301
Tell me where to find your son.

474
00:28:45.607 --> 00:28:47.051
(grunts)

475
00:28:47.075 --> 00:28:49.075
(whinnies)

476
00:28:51.613 --> 00:28:53.079
(insects buzzing)

477
00:28:57.018 --> 00:28:58.262
Ah.

478
00:28:58.286 --> 00:29:00.220
(<i> suspenseful theme playing</i>)

479
00:29:02.725 --> 00:29:05.370
(insects continue buzzing)

480
00:29:05.394 --> 00:29:07.305
(grunting)

481
00:29:07.329 --> 00:29:09.329
(whinnies)

482
00:29:10.198 --> 00:29:12.366
(grunts)

483
00:29:18.474 --> 00:29:21.052
(<i> suspenseful theme playing</i>)

484
00:29:21.076 --> 00:29:22.576
(Richard grunts)

485
00:29:24.312 --> 00:29:27.726
(whispering)
Don't make

486
00:29:27.750 --> 00:29:29.728
a sound.

487
00:29:29.752 --> 00:29:31.551
(Richard grunts softly)

488
00:29:33.489 --> 00:29:36.222
(creature screeches)

489
00:29:40.396 --> 00:29:42.228
(creature screeching)

490
00:29:45.467 --> 00:29:47.233
(creature screeching)

491
00:29:50.739 --> 00:29:52.584
(horse whinnying)

492
00:29:52.608 --> 00:29:54.619
(grunting)

493
00:29:54.643 --> 00:29:57.143
(creature screeching)

494
00:29:58.313 --> 00:30:00.580
Ah. Ugh. No!

495
00:30:06.021 --> 00:30:08.154
(screeches)

496
00:30:13.629 --> 00:30:15.629
(squealing)

497
00:30:19.802 --> 00:30:21.112
Ah!

498
00:30:21.136 --> 00:30:23.437
(gasps)

499
00:30:24.606 --> 00:30:26.339
(Kahlan sighs)

500
00:30:27.609 --> 00:30:29.621
What was that thing?

501
00:30:29.645 --> 00:30:31.122
A Gar.

502
00:30:31.146 --> 00:30:33.425
It uses the blood flies
to sniff out its prey.

503
00:30:33.449 --> 00:30:35.760
Apparently. D'Haran
soldiers weren't the only thing

504
00:30:35.784 --> 00:30:38.262
that followed you
through the Boundary.

505
00:30:38.286 --> 00:30:40.364
What did you do to it?

506
00:30:40.388 --> 00:30:42.534
Wizard's fire.

507
00:30:42.558 --> 00:30:45.692
Wasn't sure I had it in
me after all these years.

508
00:30:47.295 --> 00:30:49.474
What are you doing?
Going to find my father

509
00:30:49.498 --> 00:30:51.810
before something horrible
happens to him too.

510
00:30:51.834 --> 00:30:53.812
ZEDD: We'll go together.
No.

511
00:30:53.836 --> 00:30:56.135
Stay away from me. both of you.

512
00:30:57.840 --> 00:31:00.318
KAHLAN:
He's got the Sword
and the Book.

513
00:31:00.342 --> 00:31:03.242
Well. isn't that exactly
what you wanted?

514
00:31:05.013 --> 00:31:06.513
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

515
00:31:21.429 --> 00:31:22.707
Hyah!

516
00:31:22.731 --> 00:31:24.798
Dad!

517
00:31:31.807 --> 00:31:34.708
I'll get you.
I'll get you.

518
00:31:43.351 --> 00:31:45.697
(gasps)

519
00:31:45.721 --> 00:31:48.722
(George groaning)

520
00:31:50.592 --> 00:31:51.825
Who did this?

521
00:31:54.062 --> 00:31:56.040
The D'Haran.

522
00:31:56.064 --> 00:31:58.743
Ranssyn Fane.

523
00:31:58.767 --> 00:32:00.177
I'll take you to Zedd's.

524
00:32:00.201 --> 00:32:01.513
No.
He has potions.

525
00:32:01.537 --> 00:32:02.747
No.

526
00:32:02.771 --> 00:32:06.450
No. Fane is looking
for you there.

527
00:32:06.474 --> 00:32:10.309
You can't go back to Zedd's.

528
00:32:14.215 --> 00:32:16.115
Zedd told me...

529
00:32:18.554 --> 00:32:20.297
He said you're not my father.

530
00:32:20.321 --> 00:32:24.024
Of course I'm your father.

531
00:32:25.060 --> 00:32:27.405
Then it was a lie.

532
00:32:27.429 --> 00:32:28.728
No.

533
00:32:30.566 --> 00:32:34.267
Every word he told you is true.

534
00:32:38.339 --> 00:32:42.442
But I will always
be your father.

535
00:32:46.347 --> 00:32:48.815
(groans)

536
00:32:52.821 --> 00:32:55.822
(<i> melancholy theme playing</i>)

537
00:33:03.264 --> 00:33:04.764
Dad?

538
00:33:10.772 --> 00:33:12.739
(sobs)

539
00:33:15.611 --> 00:33:16.811
(sniffs)

540
00:33:20.115 --> 00:33:22.348
(horses approaching)

541
00:33:27.388 --> 00:33:29.000
MICHAEL:
Richard.

542
00:33:29.024 --> 00:33:31.257
We saw the smoke.

543
00:33:32.427 --> 00:33:34.405
What happened?

544
00:33:34.429 --> 00:33:35.629
He's dead.

545
00:33:43.371 --> 00:33:44.804
(sighs)

546
00:33:52.547 --> 00:33:54.792
Did the witch make you do this?

547
00:33:54.816 --> 00:33:57.328
Michael. you can't
possibly believe...

548
00:33:57.352 --> 00:33:59.797
I don't know what to believe!

549
00:33:59.821 --> 00:34:01.499
It was Ranssyn Fane.
MICHAEL: No.

550
00:34:01.523 --> 00:34:04.002
He's with Chase looking for you.

551
00:34:04.026 --> 00:34:05.424
Well. he came back!

552
00:34:06.728 --> 00:34:08.768
That sword.
Where did you get it?

553
00:34:10.331 --> 00:34:12.944
Richard. where have you been?

554
00:34:12.968 --> 00:34:15.613
Michael. he murdered our father.

555
00:34:15.637 --> 00:34:17.682
Not our father.

556
00:34:17.706 --> 00:34:19.372
My father.

557
00:34:22.978 --> 00:34:24.210
You knew.

558
00:34:27.348 --> 00:34:28.760
Why didn't you tell me?

559
00:34:28.784 --> 00:34:32.964
Because he made me
swear that I never would.

560
00:34:32.988 --> 00:34:35.633
But now he's dead.

561
00:34:35.657 --> 00:34:39.037
Did he tell you
where I came from?

562
00:34:39.061 --> 00:34:40.604
No.

563
00:34:40.628 --> 00:34:42.073
But I'm beginning to wonder.

564
00:34:42.097 --> 00:34:44.208
And until I find out

565
00:34:44.232 --> 00:34:45.376
you're not going anywhere.

566
00:34:45.400 --> 00:34:47.167
Take him.

567
00:34:50.638 --> 00:34:52.072
Stay back!

568
00:34:53.809 --> 00:34:55.787
Witchcraft.

569
00:34:55.811 --> 00:34:57.276
Fane was right.

570
00:34:58.814 --> 00:35:01.081
(<i> action theme playing</i>)

571
00:35:02.584 --> 00:35:04.104
RICHARD:
Hyah!

572
00:35:05.354 --> 00:35:07.354
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

573
00:35:10.124 --> 00:35:11.436
(horse whinnies)

574
00:35:11.460 --> 00:35:15.105
Where are you going
in such a hurry. boy?

575
00:35:15.129 --> 00:35:18.075
I'm going back to your
house to find Fane.

576
00:35:18.099 --> 00:35:19.477
He murdered my father.

577
00:35:19.501 --> 00:35:22.380
(sighs)

578
00:35:22.404 --> 00:35:25.115
I am so sorry.

579
00:35:25.139 --> 00:35:26.339
Get out of my way.

580
00:35:28.343 --> 00:35:31.411
I understand your pain.

581
00:35:34.115 --> 00:35:37.194
Richard Cypher. you were
meant for more than revenge.

582
00:35:37.218 --> 00:35:38.696
RICHARD:
You think I care what you say.

583
00:35:38.720 --> 00:35:40.231
old man?
I'm going to kill him!

584
00:35:40.255 --> 00:35:41.399
KAHLAN:
And if you fail.

585
00:35:41.423 --> 00:35:43.434
and he kills you?

586
00:35:43.458 --> 00:35:46.036
You said this Sword would
give me the power to fight evil.

587
00:35:46.060 --> 00:35:48.305
Yes. In the service
of freedom and justice.

588
00:35:48.329 --> 00:35:49.640
not your own rage.

589
00:35:49.664 --> 00:35:51.275
You're not ready
to use the Sword.

590
00:35:51.299 --> 00:35:53.177
I said get out of my way!

591
00:35:53.201 --> 00:35:54.579
Come on!

592
00:35:54.603 --> 00:35:56.113
(growls)

593
00:35:56.137 --> 00:35:58.137
(<i> exciting theme playing</i>)

594
00:36:17.392 --> 00:36:19.392
(board creaks)

595
00:36:38.112 --> 00:36:39.378
(bottle clatters)

596
00:37:08.677 --> 00:37:10.220
(chickens clucking)

597
00:37:10.244 --> 00:37:12.111
(yells)

598
00:37:18.152 --> 00:37:19.464
FANE:
Tell me where the witch is

599
00:37:19.488 --> 00:37:22.589
or I'll run you through.

600
00:37:25.226 --> 00:37:27.393
I'll never help you.

601
00:37:28.730 --> 00:37:30.575
I don't know what lies

602
00:37:30.599 --> 00:37:33.410
that witch
has put into your head.

603
00:37:33.434 --> 00:37:35.613
but ask yourself:

604
00:37:35.637 --> 00:37:38.538
Are you really prepared to die
for someone you don't even know?

605
00:37:41.409 --> 00:37:43.409
She didn't kill my father.

606
00:37:47.415 --> 00:37:49.059
You did.

607
00:37:49.083 --> 00:37:51.562
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

608
00:37:51.586 --> 00:37:53.130
(both grunting)

609
00:37:53.154 --> 00:37:54.353
(roars)

610
00:37:56.758 --> 00:37:59.993
(both grunting)

611
00:38:08.737 --> 00:38:10.102
Good!

612
00:38:21.449 --> 00:38:24.417
(both grunting)

613
00:38:28.289 --> 00:38:30.289
(clattering)

614
00:38:32.661 --> 00:38:34.005
(groans)

615
00:38:34.029 --> 00:38:36.140
Beg for your life. boy!

616
00:38:36.164 --> 00:38:37.730
Do it!

617
00:38:39.233 --> 00:38:40.377
(groans)

618
00:38:40.401 --> 00:38:43.402
Just like your father did.

619
00:38:45.173 --> 00:38:46.639
(Richard groans)

620
00:38:52.213 --> 00:38:53.991
FANE:
The Book.

621
00:38:54.015 --> 00:38:57.161
You brought me the Book.

622
00:38:57.185 --> 00:38:58.417
(chuckles)

623
00:39:01.456 --> 00:39:02.633
No.

624
00:39:02.657 --> 00:39:04.356
(<i> exciting theme playing</i>)

625
00:39:06.294 --> 00:39:07.734
FANE:
Hyah!

626
00:39:08.630 --> 00:39:10.274
No!

627
00:39:10.298 --> 00:39:12.932
(panting)

628
00:39:14.001 --> 00:39:17.381
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

629
00:39:17.405 --> 00:39:18.571
Fane!

630
00:39:19.474 --> 00:39:21.251
I'm gonna kill you!

631
00:39:21.275 --> 00:39:23.287
(panting)

632
00:39:23.311 --> 00:39:25.088
You're gonna die!

633
00:39:25.112 --> 00:39:26.712
(panting)

634
00:39:35.222 --> 00:39:36.782
KAHLAN:
Richard!

635
00:39:39.527 --> 00:39:41.171
The Book.

636
00:39:41.195 --> 00:39:42.962
Fane has it.

637
00:39:45.667 --> 00:39:48.334
(Richard panting)

638
00:39:51.639 --> 00:39:53.016
Then we failed.

639
00:39:53.040 --> 00:39:55.753
No. I failed.

640
00:39:55.777 --> 00:39:57.154
(Richard sighs)

641
00:39:57.178 --> 00:39:59.222
Not yet.

642
00:39:59.246 --> 00:40:00.658
Fane still has
to cross the Boundary

643
00:40:00.682 --> 00:40:01.992
to get the Book to Rahl.

644
00:40:02.016 --> 00:40:03.327
We can still stop him.

645
00:40:03.351 --> 00:40:04.528
Don't you get it?

646
00:40:04.552 --> 00:40:07.319
I'm not what you want me to be.

647
00:40:08.422 --> 00:40:10.400
Maybe all those years ago

648
00:40:10.424 --> 00:40:13.771
you saved the wrong child.

649
00:40:13.795 --> 00:40:16.574
(Richard panting)

650
00:40:16.598 --> 00:40:19.732
(<i> melancholy theme playing</i>)

651
00:40:24.405 --> 00:40:26.517
No.

652
00:40:26.541 --> 00:40:30.354
You are the true Seeker.

653
00:40:30.378 --> 00:40:34.358
You have a great destiny
ahead of you. Richard Cypher.

654
00:40:34.382 --> 00:40:38.183
if you're willing to accept it.

655
00:40:43.457 --> 00:40:47.259
In this life. we cannot
go back. Only forward.

656
00:40:50.297 --> 00:40:51.742
But I've lost everything.

657
00:40:51.766 --> 00:40:53.511
ZEDD:
Not everything.

658
00:40:53.535 --> 00:40:55.412
You have me.

659
00:40:55.436 --> 00:40:58.248
And Kahlan.

660
00:40:58.272 --> 00:41:01.018
And if you stop Rahl.

661
00:41:01.042 --> 00:41:03.543
then your father
and Kahlan's sister

662
00:41:05.146 --> 00:41:07.780
won't have died for nothing.

663
00:41:18.392 --> 00:41:20.593
Teach me.

664
00:41:22.163 --> 00:41:24.129
(hand pats shoulder)

665
00:41:29.704 --> 00:41:32.149
Richard Cypher.

666
00:41:32.173 --> 00:41:36.408
Will you accept
the name of the Seeker?

667
00:41:43.451 --> 00:41:45.162
I will.

668
00:41:45.186 --> 00:41:47.386
(<i> dramatic theme playing</i>)

669
00:41:56.831 --> 00:41:58.542
Then I.

670
00:41:58.566 --> 00:42:00.210
First Wizard

671
00:42:00.234 --> 00:42:03.213
Zeddicus Zu'l Zorander

672
00:42:03.237 --> 00:42:06.016
so name you.

673
00:42:06.040 --> 00:42:08.040
(<i> exciting theme playing</i>)

674
00:42:17.251 --> 00:42:19.251
(thunder crashing)

675
00:42:29.664 --> 00:42:30.975
(gasps)

676
00:42:30.999 --> 00:42:32.342
(yells)

677
00:42:32.366 --> 00:42:35.034
(panting)

678
00:42:37.404 --> 00:42:39.149
Lord Rahl?

679
00:42:39.173 --> 00:42:40.383
What is it?

680
00:42:40.407 --> 00:42:41.641
What's wrong?

681
00:42:43.577 --> 00:42:46.356
The Seeker.

682
00:42:46.380 --> 00:42:50.711
He lives.

683
00:42:50.735 --> 00:42:52.718
(<i> main theme playing</i>)
